      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Using your rescue inhaler more frequently is a dangerous sign that your asthma is out of control, not a solution to aging lungs. Increasing dosage without medical supervision can lead to severe side effects or mask a life-threatening attack until it's too late. You need a prescription for controller medication to stop this progression, which is why avoiding a doctor will only make your breathing worse.",
      "source": "target",
